citation.case_name: Keller v. Wisconsin Ex Rel. State Bar of Wis.

html:
374 U.S. 102

83 S.Ct. 1686

10 L.Ed.2d 1026

John J. KELLER
v.
WISCONSIN ex rel. STATE BAR OF WISCONSIN.

No. 429.

Supreme Court of the United States

June 10, 1963

Frank M. Coyne, for petitioner.

John W. Reynolds, Atty. Gen. of Wisconsin, and Warren H. Resh, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

On Petition for Writ of Certiorari to the Supreme Court of Wisconsin.

PER CURIAM.

1

The petition for writ of certiorari is granted, the judgment is vacated and the case is remanded to the Supreme Court of Wisconsin for reconsideration in light of Sperry v. Florida ex rel. The Florida Bar, 373 U.S. 379, 83 S.Ct. 1322.
